08842nam a22011775i 9783868598858DE-B159720210830012106.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210830t20142014gw     fo  d z      eng d  a97838685988587 a10.1515/97838685988582doi  a(DE-B1597)531373  a(OCoLC)905528663  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 4aHT166 7aARC0000002bisacsh04a307.1a307.121600aYoung Research Forum :bResearch Papers for Future Megacities on Governance, Water, Planning, and Mobility /ced. by Lukas Born. 1aBerlin : bJOVIS Verlag GmbH, c[2014] 4c©2014  a1 online resource (224 p.) :bca. 200 farb. Abb.  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aFuture Megacities00tFrontmatter -- tIndex -- tPreface and Introduction -- tThe Future Megacities Programme- Framework and Contribution of Young Researchers -- tParticipants' List of the DAAD Scholarship Programme: "Studies and Research Scholarships of Today for the Megacities of Tomorrow" -- tGovernance -- tThe Agricultural Water-Energy Nexus of Rural India under Climate Change: How Learning Coordination Becomes Key to Technology Adoption -- tImplementation of the Clean Development Mechanism (CDM) in Gauteng Municipalities: Barriers, Opportunities, and Post-2012 Outlook -- tUrban Resources: Water -- tStrategies for a Sustainable Megacity Development under the Water Resource Challenge in Urumqi Region, Northwest China -- tAuditing Water Resources for Application to Water-sensitive Urban Design-A Case Study in the Lima Metropolitan Area, Peru -- tAdaptation of the Urban Water System to Future Developments- Modelling of Different Options for Lima, Peru -- tComparison and Evaluation of Three Aquatic Plants for Determining the Efficiency of Nutrient Removal in Domestic Wastewater Treatment -- tPlanning and Architecture -- tIntegration of Environmental Components and Urban Climate Management in Land-use Planning in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam -- tLand-use Change Detection and Analysis for Ho Chi Minh City -- tMultifunctional Urban Agriculture: An Urban Planning Model for the Megacities of Tomorrow. The Case of Casablanca -- tClimate-responsive Residential Buildings for Hashtgerd New Town Based on Traditional Residential Architecture of Iran's Arid Region -- tThe Feasibility of a New Generation Office Building in Hashtgerd New Town: Modern, Efficient, and Environmentally Friendly -- tMobility and Transportation -- tTransit-Oriented Development (TOD) for Megacities: Is TOD an Effective Solution for a Megacity's Traffic Congestion? Case Study of Shenzhen, China -- tThe Public Transportation System of Hefei, China: An Analysis -- tDevelopment and Evaluation of an Airborne Traffic Detection System -- tPerspectives for Gauteng's Transportation Sector: Potential Performance and Costs of Exemplary Transportation Infrastructure Extensions -- tThe Projects of the Programme on Future Megacities in Brief -- tAuthors -- tImprint0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn addition to senior scientists, who have summarised their main results in the five volumes of the Future Megacities Book Series, ambitious young researchers have also contributed substantially to the German research programme on sustainable development of future megacities. The authors included in this volume were awarded the research programme's Young Researcher's Award in 2013, and a small but exemplary selection of their scientific work is presented here. Main topics are mobility with transit-oriented development and public transport in China, water demand and supply issues in the arid cities of Lima and Urumqi, governance questions in South Africa and India in the wide framework of energy, and improvement of urban planning procedures in Ho Chi Minh City.  aNeben hochrangigen Wissenschaftlern haben auch ambitionierte junge Forscher zu dem deutschen Forschungsprogramm zur nachhaltigen Entwicklung der Megastädte von morgen beigetragen. Dieser Band enthält eine kleine, aber exemplarische Auswahl ihrer wissenschaftlichen Arbeiten, die allesamt mit dem Young Researchers' Award des Programms von 2013 ausgezeichnet wurden. Er umfasst vier Hauptthemen: Mobilität mit transitorientierter Entwicklung und öffentlichem Verkehr in China; Wasserbedarf und -versorgungsprobleme in den trockenen Städten Lima und Urumqi; Fragen der Governance in Südafrika und Indien vor dem Hintergrund von Energieerzeugung und -versorgung; sowie die Verbesserung von Stadtplanungsverfahren in Ho-Chi-Minh-Stadt.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspects. 0aMetropolitan areasxEnvironmental aspects. 0aSustainable urban development. 4a#39. 4aAward. 4aForschung. 4aMegastädte. 4aNachhaltigkeit. 4aWissenschaft. 4aYoung Researchers. 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh  a#39.  aAward.  aForschung.  aMegastädte.  aNachhaltigkeit.  aWissenschaft.  aYoung Researchersamp.1 aAnnegarn, Harold J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorn, Lukas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBorn, Lukas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBubeck, Steffen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEltrop, Ludger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFiechtner, Manuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFricke, Katharina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKasperek, Irmgard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKimmich, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKober, Ralf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 a